    {
      "id": "4ed1d0c2_6f2ebc61",
      "file_path": "datarouter-node/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/datarouter/node/DeliveryQueue.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 315,
      "message": "Added a comment, PM Mapper will be using 429 to enable rate limiting. So if they are receiving files too quickly they can respond with 429 and get the file later",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4447,
        "name": "Conor Ward",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "conor.ward@est.tech",
        "username": "econwar"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-14 09:58:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "d956d0b2_83b75dc0",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "b829e6bc_f5ddf542",
      "file_path": "datarouter-node/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/datarouter/node/NodeServlet.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 195,
      "message": "The authorization below is checking the feed user and password which we felt was irrelevant in this case. We just check that the subscription is \"privileged\" before attempting to delete the file.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4447,
        "name": "Conor Ward",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "conor.ward@est.tech",
        "username": "econwar"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-14 09:58:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a0818ea1_dc666205",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "be079149_641a873b",
      "file_path": "datarouter-node/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/datarouter/node/NodeServlet.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 505,
      "message": "Would it be better if it stated. \"NODE0113 Error: Unable to delete X and Y from DR Node Z. Reason: Subscription <id> is not a privileged subscription\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4447,
        "name": "Conor Ward",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "conor.ward@est.tech",
        "username": "econwar"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-14 09:58:03.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "1f6587d8_5f51f86a",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "3c7c09c5_48df00a5",
      "file_path": "datarouter-node/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/datarouter/node/NodeServlet.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 505,
      "message": "I didn't have a problem so much with the wording.  Perhaps I misunderstood this function?  I thought it was determining whether the file could be deleted or not. And the legacy case is that the file would be deleted.  So it just seemed odd to log an error on the case where you determine that delete is not permitted.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 1111,
        "name": "Dominic Lunanuova",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "dgl@research.att.com",
        "username": "dglFromAtt"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-15 15:07:17.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "be079149_641a873b",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "0012508f_10827c0f",
      "file_path": "datarouter-node/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/datarouter/node/NodeServlet.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 505,
      "message": "Ah ok I see your point but is there a possibility where a file existed on the dr-node that failed to be delivered to a subscriber that wasn't \"privileged\" and some subscriber tried to use this API to delete it. That is the case that we were trying to handle here but if you feel it is not relevant we can remove it.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4447,
        "name": "Conor Ward",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "conor.ward@est.tech",
        "username": "econwar"
      },
      "updated": "2019-02-15 15:39:14.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "3c7c09c5_48df00a5",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "0f06480e_d201637b",
      "file_path": "datarouter-node/src/main/java/org/onap/dmaap/datarouter/node/NodeServlet.java",
      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 505,
      "message": "I get it!  you only get here via delete API.  It isn't a general check after any file delivery. Sorry for the confusion",
